The paper deals with the issue of blackbox deep neural networks in the context of reinforcement learning, which is a problem that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), computer vision (cs.CV), and natural language processing (cs.CL). However, since the paper focuses on the interpretability of learned features and their impact on governing agent behavior, it is most likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
